Worked on Pokedex App

Notes: 

- Make sure when passing props, not using the props keyword, like the example below, you must wrap the prop inside {} brackets. 
const NewComponent = ({uniquePropNameHere}) => {}

You can have one component export another component as a return value. 
There are two ways to check if an item exists in an array, use forEach() or map(), then use one of the options below

Check if item does NOT EXIST
if (myArr.indexOf(item) === -1) || if (!myArr.includes(item))

Check if item EXISTS 
if (myArr.indexOf(item) >= 0) || if (myArr.includes(item))
